#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:1
msgid "Domain Routing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:3
msgid "**Module:** `lu_ai_orchestrator`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:5
msgid "Domain Routing lets a single *Orchestrator* agent dispatch user messages to specialised domain agents — Sales, Finance, HR, Inventory, and more — based on keyword rules, with a configurable fallback when no rule matches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:9
msgid "For installation prerequisites and first-chat setup, see [Quick Start](quickstart.md). For agent and model configuration, see [Configuration](configuration.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:15
msgid "1. What Is an Orchestrator?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:17
msgid "A regular AI agent receives a prompt and generates a response directly using its own LLM model and system prompt.  An **Orchestrator** agent sits in front of one or more domain agents and decides which one should handle each prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:21
msgid "Orchestrator dispatching to domain agents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:21
msgid ".. image:: /_static/img/ai-agent/domain-routing-overview.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:26
msgid "Enabling the **Is Orchestrator** toggle on an agent form activates the routing layer.  The orchestrator itself may still hold an LLM model — it is used for LLM-based fallback classification and for direct responses when no rule matches."
msgstr ""

