#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:296
msgid "9. Advanced: Multi-layer Prompts (lu_ai_edge)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:298
msgid "Installing the optional `lu_ai_edge` module extends the routing layer with additional prompt assembly capabilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:301
msgid "Chain-of-Thought (CoT) instructions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:303
msgid "Each domain rule gains a CoT instruction block appended after the base system prompt.  These instructions guide the domain agent to reason step-by-step before producing an answer — particularly useful for complex financial or inventory calculations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:308
msgid "Few-shot examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:310
msgid "Domain-specific few-shot examples can be stored in `ir.config_parameter` and injected into the system prompt at routing time.  This improves consistency for structured outputs such as tables, formatted reports, or JSON payloads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:314
msgid "MMR RAG reranking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:316
msgid "When a domain agent uses RAG (document retrieval), `lu_ai_edge` replaces the default similarity-only reranking with **Maximal Marginal Relevance (MMR)**. MMR balances relevance with diversity, reducing redundant chunks when multiple documents cover similar content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:321
msgid "The MMR lambda parameter (`ai.edge.mmr_lambda`, default `0.5`) controls the relevance-diversity trade-off:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:324
msgid "`1.0` — pure relevance (same as the default ranker)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:325
msgid "`0.0` — pure diversity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:326
msgid "`0.5` — balanced (recommended starting point)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/domain-routing.md:328
msgid "Set it at **Settings → Technical → Parameters → System Parameters**."
msgstr ""

